============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Supply and Demand
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Price determined where quantity supplied equals demanded
Formula:    P* where Qd=Qs
Economist:  Alfred Marshall
Example:    Housing prices rise when population grows but supply stays fixed

Concept:    Opportunity Cost
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Value of next-best alternative foregone when choosing
Formula:    OC = forgone alternative value
Economist:  Bastiat
Example:    Studying means forgoing wages you could have earned working

Concept:    Comparative Advantage
Category:   International Trade
Definition: Countries gain by specializing in what they produce most efficiently
Formula:    Compare opportunity cost ratios
Economist:  David Ricardo
Example:    China makes electronics cheaply; USA makes pharma cheaply; both gain trading

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Utilitarianism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Maximize pleasure minimize pain across all sentient beings
Philosopher:  Jeremy Bentham
Example:      Felicific calculus: measure units of pleasure and pain

Concept:      Stoicism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Focus only on what is in your control; accept all else with equanimity
Philosopher:  Marcus Aurelius/Epictetus
Example:      Illness is not in your control; your response to it is

Concept:      Existentialism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   Existence precedes essence; radical freedom and responsibility
Philosopher:  Jean-Paul Sartre
Example:      You are not born kind or cruel; you become so through choices

